{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionWith the rapid development of next-generation sequencing technology, the cost of interpreting the clinical significance of hundreds of thousands of genomic variants has become an obvious bottleneck for genetic testing [1][2][3].",
    "There are dozens of well-established biological databases that are curated and maintained by researchers, which facilitate the interpretation of genomic variants.",
    "However, the knowledge provided by these valuable data resources is quite limited [4][5][6][7][8][9].",
    "Literature in biomedical domain still serve as a huge repository to store tremendous knowledge for genetic variant interpretation.",
    "As a result, it poses great challenge for genetic interpreters to search literature manually for relevant evidences for a given variant."
  ]
}